text: Simmons Lake is a lake in the U.S. state of Washington. The lake has a surface area of and reaches a depth of . Simmons Lake was named after Michael T. Simmons, a pioneer citizen. A variant name was "Ken Lake". ==See also== *List of lakes in Washington ==References== Category:Lakes of Thurston County, Washington Category:Lakes of Washington (state)
